Johannesburg – Award-winning musician Cassper Nyovest has recently taken to social media to show off his car collection. It is very clear that Cassper is a lover of nice things in life, and has worked very hard to accomplish all he has today. Over the weekend Cassper lent his friend Lekau Sehoana who is the founder and Director of Drip footwear his McLaren.   The musician shared that Lekau returned his McLaren safe and sound but without petrol.      Also Read: Luxury car dealership silences Cassper Nyovest’s haters For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.